An explanation of the Regex:   
`\/` - matches a literal `/`  
`[^\/]+` - matches anything other than a `/` at least once  
`(?=\.)` - a positive lookahead asserting that what immediately follows the current position in the string is a literal dot  
`\.` - matches a literal dot  
`[^?]+` matches anything that&#39;s not a literal question mark

